qas.question: What resulted in a net gain of seats?
How many seats did the Conservatives have in the House of Commons in 2015?
How many seats did the Scottish National Party lose?
Where did the Liberal Democrats gain seats?
Who was one of the Liberal Democrat challengers?

context: The <b0_0>2015 General Election<b0_0/> resulted in a net loss of seats throughout Great Britain, with Labour representation falling to <b1_0>232<b1_0/> seats in the House of Commons. The Party lost <b2_0>40<b2_0/> of its 41 seats in Scotland in the face of record breaking swings to the Scottish National Party. The scale of the decline in Labour's support was much greater than what had occurred at the 2011 elections for the Scottish parliament. Though Labour gained more than 20 seats in <b3_0>England and Wales<b3_0/>, mostly from the Liberal Democrats but also from the Conservative Party, it lost more seats to Conservative challengers, including that of <b4_0>Ed Balls<b4_0/>, for net losses overall.
